    <title>How to manage multiple git users on a single system</title>
    <link href="https://jenishjain.in/manage-multiple-git-user-on-1-system/"/>
    <updated>2022-09-02T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <id>https://jenishjain.in/manage-multiple-git-user-on-1-system/</id>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Having problems managing your multiple personalities? &lt;br /&gt;
well this can be resolved for git using these simple steps.ðŸª„&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;problem&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;Problem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most of us have atleast two github profiles one for work and another personal and contributing to both of them with separate accounts could be a pain. while one can always remember and switch their profiles, but we can do a better job here using some configurations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;solution&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;Solution&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Assuming you have a usual setup of a workspace and a personalspace which you use to organise your work and personal projects and the structure looks something like this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662190325/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-structure.png&quot; alt=&quot;folder structure&quot; srcset=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662190325/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-structure.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662190325/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-structure.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662190325/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-structure.png 680w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662190325/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-structure.png 300w&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
We can take advantage of gitconfigs here to instruct git to use a particular set of credentials in a given space.
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a &lt;em&gt;.gitconfig&lt;/em&gt; file at the root level which maintains your global git configuration. what we are gonna do is store individual git config in your pesonal and work folders and tell &lt;em&gt;.gitconfig&lt;/em&gt; to replace the user and credentials according to the space you are in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;create-space-specific-config-files&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;create space specific config files&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;we will have to create &lt;em&gt;.config&lt;/em&gt; files in each folder something like this.
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662191687/portfolio/blog-assets/git-config.png&quot; alt=&quot;git-config&quot; srcset=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662191687/portfolio/blog-assets/git-config.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662191687/portfolio/blog-assets/git-config.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662191687/portfolio/blog-assets/git-config.png 680w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662191687/portfolio/blog-assets/git-config.png 300w&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
after creating both the config files your folders should looks like this.
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192358/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-with-gitconf.png&quot; alt=&quot;folders-with-gitconfig&quot; srcset=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192358/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-with-gitconf.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192358/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-with-gitconf.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192358/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-with-gitconf.png 680w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192358/portfolio/blog-assets/folder-with-gitconf.png 300w&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;configuring-your-global-git-config&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;configuring your global git config&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;now in your global &lt;code&gt;~/.gitconfig&lt;/code&gt; file we need to replace the [user] block with the one shown below ( for me both workspace and personal space were present on desktop)
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192762/portfolio/blog-assets/global-git-config.png&quot; alt=&quot;global git config&quot; srcset=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192762/portfolio/blog-assets/global-git-config.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192762/portfolio/blog-assets/global-git-config.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192762/portfolio/blog-assets/global-git-config.png 680w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662192762/portfolio/blog-assets/global-git-config.png 300w&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;thats-all&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;Thats All ðŸŽ‰&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;now you can simply navigate to your desired space and work without worrying about commiting with correct git profile.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;test-if-this-is-working&quot; tabindex=&quot;-1&quot;&gt;Test if this is working ðŸ‘€&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;we can test this by simply creating a test project and initialising git in it. on checking the local config you should see the appropirate username and email configured.
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/personalpace-test.png&quot; alt=&quot;personalspace-test&quot; srcset=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/personalpace-test.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/personalpace-test.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/personalpace-test.png 680w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/personalpace-test.png 300w&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/workspace-test.png&quot; alt=&quot;workspace-test&quot; srcset=&quot;https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/workspace-test.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/workspace-test.png 2040w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/workspace-test.png 680w, https://res.cloudinary.com/jenishjain/image/upload/v1662193809/portfolio/blog-assets/workspace-test.png 300w&quot; loading=&quot;lazy&quot; sizes=&quot;(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
